title: Härjedalen Municipality
text:
Härjedalen Municipality (, , ) is a <a href="municipalities%20of%20Sweden">municipality</a> in <a href="J%C3%A4mtland%20County">Jämtland County</a> in northern <a href="Sweden">Sweden</a>. Its <a href="administrative%20centre">seat</a> is located in <a href="Sveg">Sveg</a>.
The municipality roughly, but not exactly, corresponds with the traditional <a href="provinces%20of%20Sweden">province</a> <a href="H%C3%A4rjedalen">Härjedalen</a>.
The municipality was created in 1974 and is one of two in Sweden with the name of a province (<a href="Gotland%20Municipality">Gotland Municipality</a> is the other). It consists of nine original local government entities (as of 1863).
Geography.
With a total area of , it is Sweden's fifth largest. However, it is largely <a href="wilderness">wilderness</a>, and the municipality is sparsely inhabited. For comparison, the municipality covers as much territory as <a href="Uppsala%20County">Uppsala County</a> and <a href="Stockholm%20County">Stockholm County</a> combined, but those two counties have over 2,000,000 inhabitants.
